ğŸ§  About the Project
LawLens is a beginner-friendly AI-powered web app that helps simplify, analyze, and understand complex legal documents. Whether you're a lawyer, student, startup founder, or someone just trying to interpret a contract â€” LawLens acts like your virtual legal assistant.

It lets users upload legal files like PDFs, DOCX, or plain text, and then performs useful AI tasks such as summarization, Q&A, fake clause detection, and named entity recognition â€” all within a sleek, Streamlit-powered UI.

ğŸš€ What It Can Do
âœ… Summarize Legal Documents
Converts dense legal text into simplified summaries in seconds using an LLM.

â“ Ask Questions About the Document
Lets you ask custom questions about the uploaded legal file and provides intelligent, contextual answers.

ğŸš¨ Detect Suspicious or Fake Clauses
Uses LLM reasoning to flag vague, unusual, or risky clauses automatically.

ğŸ“Œ Named Entity Recognition (NER)
Extracts important people, places, laws, organizations, and dates from the document using spaCy.

ğŸ“„ Export Summary and Answers
Allows you to download the summary and Q&A results in .docx format for sharing or saving.


ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack
Frontend: Streamlit (Python)

Backend & AI: OpenRouter API (Mistral LLM)

Text Extraction: pdfplumber, docx2txt, PyMuPDF

NER Engine: spaCy

Export: python-docx

Environment Handling: python-dotenv

